        </item> </list> </solution>
</exercise>
        <para id="id66031">By now you should have seen that free fall motion is just a special case of motion with constant acceleration, and we use the same equations as before. The only difference is that the value for the acceleration, <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mi>a</m:mi></m:math>, is always equal to the value of gravitational acceleration, <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mi>g</m:mi></m:math>. In the equations of motion we can replace <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mi>a</m:mi></m:math> with <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mi>g</m:mi></m:math>.</para>
