            </m:mtable>
          </m:math>
        </equation>
        </item> <item> <label> Calculate the kinetic energy. </label>
        <para id="id69467">The kinetic energy of the tree trunk at the bottom of the waterfall is equal to the potential energy it had at the top of the waterfall. Therefore <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mi>K</m:mi><m:mi>E</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>4 900</m:mn><m:mspace width="2pt"/><m:mi>J</m:mi></m:math>.</para>
        </item> <item> <label> Calculate the velocity. </label>
        <para id="id69490">To calculate the velocity of the tree trunk we need to use the equation for kinetic energy.</para>
        <equation id="id69494">
